studyName: Impact of Genomic Variation on Function (IGVF) Consortium

releaseNotes: The new data release includes over 2,000 long-read genome sequences and 12,000 short-read genome and exome analyses, nearly 400 snapshots of patient transcriptomes and epigenomes in individual cells using single-cell RNA (scRNA) and sc open chromatin (scATAC), over 3,000 bulk whole genome bisulphite genome sequences for methylome interpretation, and over 200 functional assessments in available patient tissues using full length cDNA sequences by IsoSeq (PacBio) methodology. This release also consolidates data from release 4 and 5 into a single dataset for exporting.

This new data release includes whole genome genotype data on over 30,000 Epi25 participants, generated using Illumina's Infinium GSA-MD v1 platform. Additionally, detailed clinical phenotypes related to epilepsy diagnosis are now available for both the GSA data as well as the whole exome sequencing (WES) data previously released in v3.

For a full list of the 32 consent codes see [dbGaP study page](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/projects/gap/cgi-bin/study.cgi?study_id=phs001489.v4.p2).
